[More information on this outbreak would be appreciated. As this newswire
suggests this outbreak is along the Colombia/Venezuela border, information
on possible yellow fever activity in the neighboring area in Venezuela
would be appreciated as well. Of note, in a Jan 2003 ProMED-mail posting
there was a report of the death of 22 monkeys in this area near the
Colombia Venezuela border and the possibility of yellow fever was raised at
that time. More information on the results of the testing performed in
Cucuta Colombia at that time would also be appreciated. - Mod.MPP]
